LOCALITY: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rossi, P." box="[322,522,1231,1257]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" refId="ref371591" refString="Rossi, P. (1790) Fauna Etrusca. Sistens insecta quae in provinciis Florentina et Pisana praesertim collegit. Vol. 1. Masi, Liburni [= Livorno], 348 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 128484" type="book" year="1790">Rossi (1790: 292)</bibRefCitation>
gave no 
<typeStatus box="[622,670,1231,1257]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257">type</typeStatus>
locality in the original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rossi, 1790)" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[1091,1432,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avidus">
<emphasis box="[1091,1272,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="256" pageNumber="257">Merodon avidus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rossi, P." box="[1287,1424,1231,1257]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" refId="ref371591" refString="Rossi, P. (1790) Fauna Etrusca. Sistens insecta quae in provinciis Florentina et Pisana praesertim collegit. Vol. 1. Masi, Liburni [= Livorno], 348 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 128484" type="book" year="1790">Rossi, 1790</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but presumably it is 
<collectingRegion box="[436,530,1267,1293]" country="Italy" name="Toscana" pageId="256" pageNumber="257">Tuscany</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[547,601,1267,1294]" name="Italy" pageId="256" pageNumber="257">Italy</collectingCountry>
) because the work deals with insects “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="256" pageNumber="257">in provinciis Florentina et Pisana collegit</emphasis>
[collected in provinces of Florence and Pisa]” (
<bibRefCitation author="Rossi, P." box="[818,1007,1303,1329]" pageId="256" pageNumber="257" refId="ref371591" refString="Rossi, P. (1790) Fauna Etrusca. Sistens insecta quae in provinciis Florentina et Pisana praesertim collegit. Vol. 1. Masi, Liburni [= Livorno], 348 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 128484" type="book" year="1790">Rossi 1790: 292</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
